The whole 'regulation of guns' issue is so complex I just can't make my mind up on it. (I'm certainly not advocating prohibition, that would make no sense, for the US at least where its obviously deeply rooted in popular culture.) This is a simplistic view perhaps but it comes back to the whole concept of 'you can't un-invent a thing that's in general use'. So instead you must strive for education and awareness, yes? Gotta be the way to go.<br>
