<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&gt; As an outsider in a land - still democratic - that has firearm<br>
restrictions I find the level of paranoia in US pro-gun rhetoric to<br>
be disturbing. I can understand your concerns about the State<br>
and its powers, but the facts speak for themselves - the US<br>
has gun-deaths at least 6 - 10 times higher than other Western<br>
democracies. <br>
&gt; The fact that psychotics can kill at will because of the<br>
over-supply of over-powered weapons is an issue that the<br>
pro-gun lobby has consistently overlooked.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Again, as many people do, you miss a main point of Moore's -an important finding, and exactly contrary to the anti-gun genre attributed to Moore's film:<br>
 Moore proves as a main tenet of his stance, that the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>number of guns</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> in the us per-capita or in-toto has no correlation to the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>number of gun deaths</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
 Simply saying that the US has a lot of guns, and a lot of crimes with guns, isn't valid. The higher population in the US compared to the number of guns and crimes does not draw us to the conclusion that the nuumber of guns drives the number of gun crimes up.<br>
One of Moore's main conclusions is that the number of guns has nothing to do with the number of crimes. He says there is something deeper going on, something even more scary than guns. The US just is nutso, and there's an unhealthy cultural thing which makes some of us go off against each other.<br>
 Thus, many people (but not Moore himself in the movie) take it to mean that the poor dumb sheeple need to be protected from themselves, and since many sheeple are afraid of the nasty guns, they're a natural target for enacting involuntary rules on what the idiot citizens should have within hands' reach.<br>
<br>
Before you agree with the gun prohibition anyway, read again the stats I mentioned above:<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:large;">*</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Vast majority of crimes do not involve a gun,<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:large;">*</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> vastly higher number of innocent law abiding and justified uses of guns to stop crimes than any number of gun-related deaths (Suicide, accident, or deliberate crime),<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:large;">*</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> vanishingly small number of private citizens using guns in defense causing collateral damage, Much smaller percentage than with police using guns, and causing collateral or regrettable damage or harm<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:large;">*</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> vanishingly small number of legally bought guns used unjustly (suicide, accident, or crime)<br>
<br>
and don't forget<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:large;">*</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> after gun prohibition passed in the UK or OZ, crime skyrocketed up, and even <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>gun crime</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> went up!<br>
Prohibition doesn't work! Anywhere, ever!<br>
<br>
I also like another statistic which goes against the idea that government agents are the only trustworthy ones to have guns:<br>
