<br>
The Second Amendment to the Constitution: &quot;A well-regulated Militia, being necessary to the security of a free State, the right of the people to keep and bear Arms, shall not be infringed.&quot;<br>
<br>
A well regulated Militia... this stems from the 18th Century when each state had its own militia. Well-regulated means training, exercises, and was a form of compulsory military service. A Militia is not the populace at large. The Second Amendment is an anachronism. I don't believe the founding fathers had 14-year olds with 30 round clips in their knock-off AK-47's mowing down their classmates in their minds. And neither do you, if you're honest. Unless those damn Canadians are plotting an invasion... Sorry for the history lesson, but I hear there are problems with your education system. Plenty of money for metal detectors to stop kids carrying guns into school, but not so much for books, or teachers, or maintenance... <br>
<br>
As for Democracy - my what short memories you have! Seem to have been a few problems down in Florida a while back as I recall - hope you're enjoying democracy under George W. <br>
<br>
Comfort blankets: It's not a healthy thing when a supposed adult can only find comfort and assurance from an inanimate object. Shows an inability to make adult relationships and live fully in the real world. May also indicate a retreat into a fantasy world, delusions and psychosis. That's why children are weaned off them at an early age - its not healthy. Go ask your imaginary friend about it.<br>
<br>
