So much for free speech. Further, I neither claim psychic powers, or that you are a dick, though both may or may not be true - I don't know. The point, which was lost, is that clinging to objects or beliefs to provide oneself with a sense of security, is not a healthy way of life. Guns won't give you security - that's a self-evident fact. They will give you an illusion of security, a belief that gun ownership is an answer to a problem, which they aren't. This is a dangerous illusion - the point being the illusion is only removed under the most extreme circumstances. <br>
<br>
As MarkIX rightly points out, having an armed populace is no remedy for the erosion of rights by a government. Your rights are being eroded every day. Goverment won't flinch from enacting draconian or unpopular laws because they fear a mass armed revolt, but they will when democratic rights are properly exercised. Democracy at the point of a gun is not democracy. Democracy only works when the ones in power realise that they are there because of a popular mandate - a mandate which can be revoked. You have that right already. [Goes on to make case for compulsory voting... ]<br>
Along with rights come responsibilities - you are responsible for your fellow man, like it or not. Putting guns into people's hands, in the belief that it guarantees security, freedom or good goverment is not a responsible action.<br>
