On a personal note, I am well acquainted with guns. I've been shooting, for vermin control and sport. I've also been shot at. It's not something I'd recommend, if you appreciate clean underwear. If you want a gun for security, or to protect your rights, you better be prepared to use it on another human being, and take the consequences. That's the only purpose of a gun - it's a weapon. Unlike a knife, or a stick, which have other legitimate uses, a gun does not. If you have a gun, you better be prepared to step over a line and know that you may have to use it. I'm not sure I could do that. I hope you're not sure either, for all our sakes.<br>
